<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,258,391]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,258,283]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Coxae all yellow expect mid coxae with 1 short black stripe. Cercus black, broadly expanded basally; both branches with strong marginal bristles ventrally; ventral branch wide but extremely short; dorsal branch rodlike, 1.2 times as long as epandrium, with 3 apical digitations, each with 1 long strong apical bristle as long as cercus. Phallus mostly pale but with a dark, blunt, convex apex.
</paragraph>
